        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1956-08-25T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1956-08-25T00:00:00-05:00" n="93"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d93">
                <head>93. Memorandum From the Under Secretary of State (<persName corresp="#p_HHJ1"
                        type="from">Hoover</persName>) to the Assistant Secretary of State for
                    Inter-American Affairs (<persName corresp="#p_HHF1" type="to"
                        >Holland</persName>)<note n="1" type="source" xml:id="d93fn1">Source:
                        Department of State, Central Files, 720.5–<gloss target="#t_MSP1"
                            >MSP</gloss>/8–2556. Confidential.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1956-08-25">
                            <hi rend="italic">August 25, 1956</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>I discussed with Mr. <persName corresp="#p_HJB1">Hollister</persName> over the
                    telephone this morning the situation with regard to the split that has developed
                    between State and <gloss target="#t_ICA1">ICA</gloss> over the <gloss
                        target="#t_ICA1">ICA</gloss> program in Latin America for the next three
                    years.</p>
                <p>Mr. <persName corresp="#p_HJB1">Hollister</persName> disagreed with the action
                    taken by Mr. <persName corresp="#p_FGDA1">FitzGerald</persName> in the Planning
                    Board and agreed with the State position which outlined a tapering off of the
                    grant assistance program during the <pb facs="0432" n="398" xml:id="pg_398"/>
                    next three year period and placing emphasis on expanded activities of loaning
                    agencies such as the <gloss target="#t_EXIMBankEximbank1">Eximbank</gloss>,
                        <gloss target="#t_IBRD1">IBRD</gloss> and <gloss target="#t_IFC1"
                        >IFC</gloss>.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_HHJ1">
                            <hi rend="strong">Herbert Hoover, Jr.</hi>
                        </persName>
                        <note n="2" xml:id="d93fn2">Printed from a copy which bears this typed
                            signature.</note>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
